E="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Casters, stand together!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Greetings all, I was at the general discussion board today, and noticed a post that seems to be quite typical of the discussions I've seen.  It involves one member of a caster class (in this case wizards, but that's not the point) comparing attributes to another class, and then complaining about a lack of balance.  Subsequently members of the compared class reply with either a well thought out post, or (more commonly) a flame.  Example:<br>
<br>
Wizard A, &quot;Mages get comperable nukes as us wizards, and at level 34 even better!  Plus they get pets, DS, etc.  Aren't we the DD masters?  Well this proves that we aren't balanced!&quot;<br>
<br>
Mage A, &quot;No, because my pet is often a liability, and my nukes are more often resisted.  You get Lures to compensate, plus you get ports!  Fact is, we can't get into groups like the Enchanters with the CC, Clarity, etc. and they get pets!  They are group gods!&quot;<br>
<br>
Enchanter A, &quot;Excuse me?  My spells are magic based and resisted like crazy!  In the high MR Uber Mobs, I can't land a thing!  And don't get me started on the worthless pet we get!&quot;<br>
<br>
Okay, you get the idea!  Does this sound at all familiar?!  Part of the problem is by game implementation of the classes.  The way I saw the casters when I started was sort of like a tree model.  We all start out fairly similar (the trunk so to speak) but as we advance in levels, each of the classes would specialize in their art and become very distinct from one another (like the outermost tree branches).  This is not the case in EverQuest, and while I think it hurts all of the casters, in my opinion the wizard class took the brunt of it since damage spells are so easy to come up with and hand out.  Personally I don't want to do damage.  If I did, I wouldn't have chosen an enchanter (I feel this class has faired the best in all the blending and muddying that has happened).<br>
<br>
So why stand together?  Because in my not so humble opinion the casters are slowly being crushed by the melee classes.  Even the enchanters are feeling it with the super high resists of Velious.  Yes I know, we get group buffs so our presence is still desired, but I have tasted the power of CC and I don't want to let it go!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Since I don't play a wizard I can't imagine what it is like.  I would hazard a guess that the majority of people who bash another caster class haven't played that class in order to know what it is really like, and so base their opinions on numbers and/or seeing someone else play the class.  Okay, I'll get off the soapbox now (although the view is lovely! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  I hope we can get Verant to listen to our problems and not only fix those of the individual classes, but those that plague us all.<br>
<br>
